Fix spurious autopoint errors when using gettext 1.0 by hiding the macros from
autopoint with added quoting.

autopoint: *** found more than one invocation of AM_GNU_GETTEXT_REQUIRE_VERSION
autopoint: *** Stop.

autopoint: *** found more than one invocation of AM_GNU_GETTEXT_VERSION
autopoint: *** Stop.

autopoint: *** AM_GNU_GETTEXT without 'external' argument is no longer supported in version 1.0
autopoint: *** Stop.

There's no upstream mention of this because gnome-online-accounts dropped their
autotools build system long before the release of gettext 1.0 but it's the same
issue encountered by other projects e.g. gnutls here:

https://gitlab.com/gnutls/gnutls/-/work_items/1792
--- configure.ac.orig	2022-03-30 09:45:03.000000000 -0500
+++ configure.ac	2026-03-20 10:34:39.000000000 -0500
@@ -470,13 +470,13 @@
 AC_DEFINE_UNQUOTED([GETTEXT_PACKAGE],["$GETTEXT_PACKAGE"],[gettext domain])
 
 # FIXME: Remove AM_GNU_GETTEXT_VERSION once autoreconf supports REQUIRE_VERSION
-AX_REQUIRE_DEFINED([AM_GNU_GETTEXT_VERSION])
+AX_REQUIRE_DEFINED([AM_GNU_GET][TEXT_VERSION])
 AM_GNU_GETTEXT_VERSION([0.19.8])
 
-AX_REQUIRE_DEFINED([AM_GNU_GETTEXT_REQUIRE_VERSION])
+AX_REQUIRE_DEFINED([AM_GNU_GET][TEXT_REQUIRE_VERSION])
 AM_GNU_GETTEXT_REQUIRE_VERSION([0.19.8])
 
-AX_REQUIRE_DEFINED([AM_GNU_GETTEXT])
+AX_REQUIRE_DEFINED([AM_GNU_GET][TEXT])
 AM_GNU_GETTEXT([external])
 
 # goaconfig.h
